<div class="page-header">
    <h1>ujTowTruck Documentation <small>Collaborative Features for Jamroom 5</small></h1>
</div>

<p>
A Mozilla service for your website that makes it surprisingly easy to collaborate in real-time.
</p>

<p>
TowTruck lets users communicate, co-author, co-browse and guide each other.
</p>

<p>
<strong>Note:</strong>
TowTruck is <strong>alpha-quality software</strong>. We do not recommend using it in production at this time.
</p>

<h3>Real-time authoring</h3>
<p>Work together at the same time and see changes made instantly.</p>

<h3>Real-time chat</h3>
<p>Talk to your friends over chat, so you can share resources and links.</p>

<h3>Real-time voice chat</h3>
<p>Using Web Real-Time Communication, you can talk with your friends over the microphone in the browser.</p>


<div class="page-header">
    <h1>Installation</h1>
</div>

<p>
Upload the module to your server.
</p>
<p>
Add the smarty function to the desired template, we use footer.tpl in the active skin directory.
</p>
<p>
Go to the module info tab in the admin control panel and enable it.
</p>
<p>
Go to the quota tab and enable TowTruck for the intended quota.
</p>



